# Task Decomposition and Assignment Plan for RestaurantReservation Web Application

## Overview
The project involves developing a comprehensive web application named "RestaurantReservation" with 9 main pages, data storage in text files, and specific frontend and backend requirements. The development language is Python. The project requires efficient, modular, and maintainable code with clear routing and data handling.

---

## 1. Project Structure and Main Tasks

### 1.1 Frontend Development (HTML + JS)
- Develop frontend pages with specified elements and IDs.
- Implement navigation and UI interactions.
- Ensure pages correspond to backend routes.

### 1.2 Backend Development (Python)
- Implement routing for all pages.
- Handle data reading/writing from/to text files.
- Implement business logic for reservations, waitlist, reviews, user profile, etc.

### 1.3 Data Management
- Design and implement data parsing and storage for:
  - Users (`users.txt`)
  - Menu items (`menu.txt`)
  - Reservations (`reservations.txt`)
  - Waitlist (`waitlist.txt`)
  - Reviews (`reviews.txt`)

---

## 2. Detailed Task Breakdown

### 2.1 Dashboard Page
- **Description**: Main hub displaying upcoming reservations and navigation buttons.
- **Frontend**:
  - Container div for dashboard.
  - Display welcome message with username.
  - Buttons: Make Reservation, View Menu, My Reservations, My Reviews, Waitlist, Profile.
- **Backend**:
  - Route: `/dashboard`
  - Fetch upcoming reservations for logged-in user.
  - Provide data for frontend display.
- **Assigned to**: Frontend Dev 1 (FE1), Backend Dev 1 (BE1)

---

### 2.2 Menu Page
- **Description**: Display restaurant menu categories and dishes.
- **Frontend**:
  - Container div for menu.
  - Grid display of dish cards with details.
  - Buttons to view dish details and back to dashboard.
- **Backend**:
  - Route: `/menu`
  - Read `menu.txt` and send data to frontend.
- **Assigned to**: FE1, BE1

---

### 2.3 Dish Details Page
- **Description**: Show detailed info about a selected dish.
- **Frontend**:
  - Container div for dish details.
  - Display dish name, description, ingredients, dietary info, avg rating.
  - Back to menu button.
- **Backend**:
  - Route: `/dish/<dish_id>`
  - Fetch dish details from `menu.txt`.
- **Assigned to**: FE1, BE1

---

### 2.4 Make Reservation Page
- **Description**: Form for users to make a table reservation.
- **Frontend**:
  - Input fields: guest name, party size (dropdown), reservation date.
  - Buttons: Submit reservation, Back to dashboard.
- **Backend**:
  - Route: `/make_reservation`
  - Validate and save reservation to `reservations.txt`.
- **Assigned to**: FE2, BE2

---

### 2.5 My Reservations Page
- **Description**: Display all reservations made by the user.
- **Frontend**:
  - List reservations with date, time, party size, status.
  - Buttons to cancel upcoming reservations.
  - Back to dashboard button.
- **Backend**:
  - Route: `/my_reservations`
  - Read `reservations.txt` filtered by user.
  - Handle cancellation requests.
- **Assigned to**: FE2, BE2

---

### 2.6 Waitlist Page
- **Description**: Display waitlist status and allow joining.
- **Frontend**:
  - Container div for waitlist.
  - Dropdown to select party size.
  - Button to join waitlist.
  - Display current waitlist position.
  - Back to dashboard button.
- **Backend**:
  - Route: `/waitlist`
  - Read/write `waitlist.txt`.
- **Assigned to**: FE2, BE2

---

### 2.7 My Reviews Page
- **Description**: Display all reviews written by the user.
- **Frontend**:
  - Container div for reviews list.
  - Button to write new review.
  - Back to dashboard button.
- **Backend**:
  - Route: `/my_reviews`
  - Read `reviews.txt` filtered by user.
- **Assigned to**: FE3, BE3

---

### 2.8 Write Review Page
- **Description**: Form to write a new review.
- **Frontend**:
  - Dropdown to select dish.
  - Rating input (stars).
  - Textarea for review text.
  - Buttons: Submit review, Back to my reviews.
- **Backend**:
  - Route: `/write_review`
  - Save review to `reviews.txt`.
- **Assigned to**: FE3, BE3

---

### 2.9 User Profile Page
- **Description**: View and edit user profile information.
- **Frontend**:
  - Display username (read-only).
  - Editable fields for other info.
  - Buttons: Save profile, Back to dashboard.
- **Backend**:
  - Route: `/profile`
  - Read/write `users.txt`.
- **Assigned to**: FE3, BE3

---

## 3. Data File Implementation Tasks

### 3.1 Users Data (`users.txt`)
- Implement reading and updating user info.
- Assigned to: BE3

### 3.2 Menu Data (`menu.txt`)
- Implement reading menu items.
- Assigned to: BE1

### 3.3 Reservations Data (`reservations.txt`)
- Implement reading, adding, cancelling reservations.
- Assigned to: BE2

### 3.4 Waitlist Data (`waitlist.txt`)
- Implement reading, adding, updating waitlist entries.
- Assigned to: BE2

### 3.5 Reviews Data (`reviews.txt`)
- Implement reading, adding reviews.
- Assigned to: BE3

---

## 4. Workflow and Task Dependencies

```mermaid
graph TD
  A[Dashboard Page] --> B[Menu Page]
  B --> C[Dish Details Page]
  A --> D[Make Reservation Page]
  A --> E[My Reservations Page]
  A --> F[Waitlist Page]
  A --> G[My Reviews Page]
  G --> H[Write Review Page]
  A --> I[User Profile Page]

  BE1 --> A
  BE1 --> B
  BE1 --> C

  BE2 --> D
  BE2 --> E
  BE2 --> F

  BE3 --> G
  BE3 --> H
  BE3 --> I

  FE1 --> A
  FE1 --> B
  FE1 --> C

  FE2 --> D
  FE2 --> E
  FE2 --> F

  FE3 --> G
  FE3 --> H
  FE3 --> I
```

---

## 5. Summary of Assignments

| Task                      | Frontend Dev | Backend Dev | Notes                          |
|---------------------------|--------------|-------------|--------------------------------|
| Dashboard Page            | FE1          | BE1         |                                |
| Menu Page                 | FE1          | BE1         |                                |
| Dish Details Page         | FE1          | BE1         |                                |
| Make Reservation Page     | FE2          | BE2         |                                |
| My Reservations Page      | FE2          | BE2         |                                |
| Waitlist Page             | FE2          | BE2         |                                |
| My Reviews Page           | FE3          | BE3         |                                |
| Write Review Page         | FE3          | BE3         |                                |
| User Profile Page         | FE3          | BE3         |                                |
| Users Data Handling       | -            | BE3         |                                |
| Menu Data Handling        | -            | BE1         |                                |
| Reservations Data Handling| -            | BE2         |                                |
| Waitlist Data Handling    | -            | BE2         |                                |
| Reviews Data Handling     | -            | BE3         |                                |

---

## 6. Additional Notes

- Each frontend developer is responsible for the HTML and JS of their assigned pages.
- Each backend developer handles routing, data parsing, and business logic for their assigned pages and data files.
- Data files are stored in the `data/` directory with pipe `|` delimiter.
- The web server should run on port 5000.
- Routing must correspond to frontend pages.
- Code should be modular and maintainable.
- Subtasks should be kept small (less than 3 per developer) and merged if necessary.

